                                <condition>Barry (1891, 524) noted that the stone was 58 inches (1.47m) in height. All of the ogham stones in the UCC collection underwent conservation in 2006. The stones are currently in display cases and held in position by brackets. The current visible extent above the display case is 1.21m.</condition>
                            </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout style="vertical" rend="arris_up">The inscription begins 0.71m (28 in.) from the bottom (Barry 1891, 524) on the dexter edge. The final three notches are duplicated on the adjacent edges of the top.</layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc>
